# XPlainVerse Challenge — Persistent Context

## What the Challenge Is

ACM Multimedia 2026 Grand Challenge on **explainable deepfake detection**.

- **Task 1:** Binary classification — is the image `real` or `fake`?
- **Task 2:** Generate two grounded NL explanations per image:
  - `complex_explanation` — detailed, technical, grounded in visible artifacts
  - `simple_explanation` — short, accessible, same core reason

**Key dates:**
- 26 May 2026 — submission opens (2 days away as of session)
- 15 Jun 2026 — final submission deadline
- 30 Jun 2026 — paper deadline (on-site presentation required at ACM-MM)

## Dataset (XPlainVerse)

| Split | Images | Real | Fake |
|---|---|---|---|
| Train | 450,000 | 130k | 320k |
| Val | 110,000 | 50k | 60k |

Located at: `/shared/workspace/lrv/luka/XPlainVerse-ACMChallenge/data/XPlainVerse/`
Val ground truth: `evaluation/data/val_ground_truth.jsonl` (110,012 rows)

## Scoring (Task 2)

**Complex explanation** (`complex_overall_score`):
- 30% `complex_bert_f1` (BERTScore vs. reference)
- 40% `complex_entity_f1` (Qwen3.5-4B extracts entities, checks bidirectional coverage)
- 30% `complex_facts_f1` (same for evidence claims)

**Simple explanation** (`simple_overall_score`):
- 70% `simple_bert_f1` (BERTScore)
- 30% `simple_sle_score` normalized (liamcripwell/sle-base — rewards short, simple language)

## Models (both already downloaded)

| Model | Path | Model type |
|---|---|---|
| Qwen3-VL-8B-XPlainVerse | `baseline_models/Qwen3-VL-8B-XPlainVerse` | `qwen3_vl` |
| InternVL3.5-14B-XPlainVerse | `baseline_models/InternVL3_5-14B-XPlainVerse` | `internvl3_5` |

HuggingFace: `kartik060702/Qwen3-VL-8B-XPlainVerse`, `kartik060702/InternVL3_5-14B-XPlainVerse`

Fine-tuned with LoRA (rank 16, alpha 32) on 260k balanced samples (1 epoch), then LoRA-merged.
Training used one `<reasoning>` + `<answer>` format — **not** separate simple/complex fields.

